# Claude Code Tools and Notes for Empirical Research

Templates and scripts for setting up empirical research projects that work well with [Claude Code](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code/overview). Designed for academic researchers who use R, work with large datasets, and want a reproducible project structure that maintains continuity across Claude Code sessions.

## The Problem This Solves

Claude Code sessions don't persist. Every time you start a new conversation, Claude has no memory of what happened in the last one. If your project doesn't have clear structure and documentation, you lose time re-explaining context, Claude makes conflicting decisions across sessions, and things quietly break.

This repo provides two things to fix that:

1. **A `CLAUDE_TEMPLATE.md`** вЂ” a set of permanent instructions that Claude reads at the start of every session. It defines ground rules (don't touch raw data, don't delete files, always ask before acting), code conventions, and a progress log system that carries context across sessions.

2. **A project setup script** вЂ” available in both PowerShell (Windows) and Bash (Mac/Linux). It creates a standardised directory structure, copies in the template files, and gives you a clean starting point.

## What's in This Repo

```
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ README.md                  # This file
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ CLAUDE_TEMPLATE.md         # Template: Claude Code session instructions
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ gitignore_template         # Template: .gitignore for R research projects
