## Quick Start

### 1. Install Git (if you don't have it)

- **Windows:** Download from https://git-scm.com/download/win and run the installer. Accept all defaults.
- **Mac:** Open Terminal and type `git --version`. If it's not installed, macOS will prompt you to install it.

### 2. Clone this repo somewhere convenient

**PowerShell (Windows):**
```powershell
git clone https://github.com/aspi6246/2026-Claude-Code-NewProject.git "$HOME\Templates\claude-tools"
```

**Bash (Mac/Linux):**
```bash
git clone https://github.com/aspi6246/2026-Claude-Code-NewProject.git ~/Templates/claude-tools
```

### 3. (Windows only) Allow PowerShell to run scripts

PowerShell blocks scripts by default. Run this once:

```powershell
Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser
```

Type `Y` when prompted.

### 4. Create a new project

**PowerShell (Windows):**
```powershell
& "$HOME\Templates\claude-tools\setup_project.ps1" -ProjectName "My-New-Paper" -DestPath "C:\Users\163178\Dropbox\1. Projects with Claude access"
```

**Bash (Mac/Linux):**
```bash
bash ~/Templates/claude-tools/setup_project.sh My-New-Paper ~/Dropbox/Research
```

This creates the full project directory structure, copies in the CLAUDE.md template and .gitignore, creates a starter README.md, and adds .gitkeep files so Git preserves empty directories.

### 5. Fill in the placeholders

Open `CLAUDE.md` in the new project folder (RStudio, VS Code, or any text editor) and replace every `XXXX`, `AUTHOR_NAME`, and `INSERT` with the real project details. Do the same for `README.md`.

### 6. Initialise Git and start working

**PowerShell:**
```powershell
cd "C:\Users\163178\Dropbox\1. Projects with Claude access\My-New-Paper"
git init; git add -A; git commit -m "Initial project structure"
claude
```

**Bash:**
```bash
cd ~/Dropbox/Research/My-New-Paper
git init && git add -A && git commit -m "Initial project structure"
claude
```

Claude reads your CLAUDE.md automatically. You're working.

---

## The Project Structure

Every project created by the setup script has this layout:

```
My-New-Paper/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ CLAUDE.md                  # Instructions for Claude (read every session)
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ README.md                  # Project overview for humans
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ .gitignore                 # Keeps build artifacts and large files out of Git
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Code/
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ _Archive/              # Superseded scripts (never deleted, moved here)
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ _Claude Logs/          # Session progress logs (key for continuity)
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ _Claude Scripts/       # Purled .R copies of Claude's .Rmd scripts
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ _Archive/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Data/
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Raw/                   # Original source data (permanently read-only)
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ Processed/             # Cleaned and constructed datasets
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ _Archive/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Output/
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Tables/                # LaTeX tables, CSVs
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ _Archive/
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ Figures/               # PDFs, PNGs
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ _Archive/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Literature/                # Reference papers and data documentation
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Paper/                     # LaTeX paper and .bib files
в””в”Ђв”Ђ Admin/                     # Notes, ideas, miscellaneous
```

### Key Design Decisions

**`_Archive/` subfolders instead of deletion.** Nothing is ever deleted. When a script, dataset, or output is superseded, it gets moved to the `_Archive/` folder within the same directory. You can always recover old work.

**`_Claude Logs/` for session continuity.** At the end of each Claude Code session, Claude writes a progress log documenting what was done, what decisions were made, and what's still pending. The next session reads these logs first, so context carries over even though Claude's memory doesn't.

**`Data/Raw/` is read-only by convention.** Original data is never modified. All transformations happen in code and write to `Data/Processed/`. This keeps the pipeline reproducible.

**Numbered scripts for pipeline order.** Scripts in `Code/` are prefixed `01_`, `02_`, etc. to indicate execution order. This makes the dependency chain explicit.

## How the CLAUDE.md Template Works

Claude Code automatically reads any `CLAUDE.md` file in the project root at the start of a session. The template includes:

- **Session startup checklist** вЂ” tells Claude to read progress logs before doing anything
- **Ground rules** вЂ” don't delete files, don't touch raw data, always confirm before acting
- **Working relationship** вЂ” defines Claude as a thinking partner who should push back and critique
- **Code conventions** вЂ” R, data.table, fixest, arrow; naming conventions; pipeline structure
- **Output conventions** вЂ” where tables, figures, and scripts go
- **Progress log protocol** вЂ” how to write and name session logs

You customise this for each project by filling in the placeholder text (`XXXX`, `AUTHOR_NAME`).

## Requirements

- Git
- [Claude Code](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code/overview)
- **Windows:** PowerShell (already installed on all Windows machines)
- **Mac/Linux:** Bash (already installed)

